A study conducted by scientists at the National Foundation for Scotland (NTS) will follow ordinary and wetland dwarf bats, as well as brown long-moved and river bats at Inverewe Gardens in Wester Ross.
Special recorders will be set up in key locations around the property to track bat activity throughout the season.
NTS staff and volunteers will also conduct mobile inspections using handheld detectors.
